The paper deals with point set registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of probabilistic methods and the focus on handling density variations suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of Expectation Maximization and the probabilistic model also suggest that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of Lidar data and the focus on real-world applications suggest that the paper could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
